# objectValue

**Instance Property**

The object that represents the cell data.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor var objectValue: Any? { get set }
```

## Discussion

The `objectValue` is automatically set by the table when using bindings or is the object returned by the [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSTableViewDataSource] protocol method [doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSTableViewDataSource/tableView(_:objectValueFor:row:)].
